        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "3082dac8981df78b",
        "text": "The basis of PBL lies in the authenticity or real-life application of the research. Students working as a team are given a \"driving question\" to respond to or answer, then directed to create an artifact (or artifacts) to present their gained knowledge. Artifacts may include a variety of media such as writings, art, drawings, three-dimensional representations, videos, photography, or technology-based presentations."
